               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers and Litanies (fols. 3r-19ra l.10)
 II)
                     Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse "Ordinary of the Mass" (fols. 19ra l.11–53rb l.8)
 III)
                     Anaphoras (fols. 53rb–143vb)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 53rb
                     l.9–66va l.9)
 III-2) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 66va
                     l.10–69vb l.11)
 III-3) Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa
                     (fols. 69vb l.13–79rb l.14)
 III-4) Anaphora of St John, son of Thunder
                     (fols. 79va l.1–88ra l.22)
 III-5) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom (fols.
                     88rb l.2–93ra l.22)
 III-6) Anaphora of St Epiphanius (fols. 93rb l.1–99ra
                     l.10)
 III-7) Anaphora of St Dioscorus (fols. 99ra l.12 –100vb l.20)
                     III-8) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 101ra l.4–108vb
                     l.1)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 108va l.2–113vb
                     l.21)
 III-10) Anaphora of St Athanasius (fols. 114ra l.1–123rb l.1)
                     III-11) Anaphora of St Gregory (fols. 123rb l.3–128vb l.3) 
 III-12)
                     Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea (fols. 128va l.5–135vb l.8)
 III-13)
                     Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols. 135vb l.10–141ra l.15)
 III-14)
                     Second Anaphora of St Gregory (fols. 141ra l.16–143vb l.20)
 
 Additio
                     1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">


                     <note>- In this Ms., the Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse (“Ordinary of the mass”) is divided
                        into two parts: the text preceding the initial monition of the priest
                        (Mimäṭän...) ends on <locus target="#26vb">26vb</locus> l.7; the Mimäṭän...
                        and the following texts are written as a separate text unit beginning on
                           <locus target="#27ra">27ra</locus> l.1.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
