                           <item>ቡራ፡ for ቡራኬ፡</item>
                           <item>እማ፡ for እማሬ፡</item>
                           <item>ተሣ፡ for እግዚኦ፡ ተሣሀለነ፡</item>
                           <item>ጸሎፈት፡ for ጸሎተ፡ ፈትቶ፡</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓ፡ ዓ፡ አ።</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን። </expan> (e.g.,
                                 <locus target="#135vb">135vb</locus> l.8)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>እግ፡ አም፡ አኃ፡ ኵ፡ ዘ፡ ለ፡ ዓ፡ አቡ፡ ለእ፡ ወ፡ ኢ፡ ክ። and similar
                                 variants</abbr> for <expan>እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላክነ፡ አኃዜ፡ ኵሉ፡ ዘለዓለም፡ አቡሁ፡
                                 ለእግዚእነ፡ ወመድኀኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ። </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#12rb">12rb</locus> ll.18-20)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the reigning monarch; a few
                           lines on the incipit page of all texts; initial words of sections and
                           structural parts of texts; most of the abbreviations; elements of the
                           punctuation signs; some of the musical notation signs above the lines;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
