                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#145r">f. 145r</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#145r">145r</locus>: ዛቲ፡ ቅዳሴ፡ ዘእሁነ፡ {ብርሃነ፡} መስቀል፡ ወአቡሁ፡
                              ወልደ፡ ኪሮስ፡ ወእሙ፡ ወለተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወአኃዊሁ፡ አቡነ፡ ተወልደ፡ መድኅን፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ መድኅን፡ አቡነ፡
                              ዘሚካኤል፡ አቡነ፡ ገብረ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ገብረ፡ መስቀል፡ ዘአጥረያ፡ በንዋዩ፡ በ፳ወ፬፡ ብር፡ ወወሀቦ፡
                              ለታቦተ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ቂርቆስ፡ ዑራ፡ ከመ፡ ትኩኖ፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት። በመንግሥተ፡ ንጉሥ፡ ምኒልክ፡
                              ወጳጳስ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወገበዝ፡ ቄስ፡ ወልደ፡ ማርያም፡ ዘሰረቃ፡ ወዘፈሃቃ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡
                              ለይኩን።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#145r">145r</locus>: This Missal belongs to our brother
                              {Bǝrhāna} Masqal; and his father (is) Walda Kiros and his mother
                              Walatta Mikāʾel and his brothers ʾabuna Tawalda Madḫǝn, ʾabuna Gabra
                              Madḫǝn, ʾabuna Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer Gabra Masqal, he (Bǝrhāna Masqal)
                              who acquired it through his own property for 24 Bǝrr and donated it to
                              the tabot of St Qirqos of ʿUra, so that it may be his guide to the
                              Kingdom of Heaven. In the reign of King Mǝnilǝk, Metropolitan Ṗeṭros
                              and gabaz (is) qes Walda Māryām. He who stole (this book) or erased
                              (its text) will be excommunicated by the authority of Peter and
                              Paul.</quote>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The concluding sentences of the Anaphoras are sometimes
                           not written out in full, with only the initial words standing for the
                           whole sentence (e.g., <locus target="#69vb">69vb</locus> l.11; 88ra
                           ls.21-22).
 - Supplication, written in the same hand as Additio 1:
                              <locus target="#85rb">85rb</locus>.
 - Minor notes: <locus target="#1v">1v</locus> (pen trial?) 21r, 102v, 142v.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
